rep, so I should probably simplify by using ls and maybe a tree command. To narrow down the file names, I think using find and then piping it to head could help me see the top results. There’s a lot to navigate here, but I’m figuring it out!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cmdI4PDLOitoyQwg2pqhSMD8|fc_06c3af14b50a39800169e186b41d88819bb29d28cb75d0f832","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/Downloads/OpenClaw-Skills/stock-analysis-6.2.0 -maxdepth 3 -type f | head -n 200","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent","timeout":20},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"find /Users/ling/Downloads/OpenClaw-Skills/stock-analysis-6.2.0 -maxdepth 3 -type f | head -n 200\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent\",\"timeout\":20}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"beecode","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":36026,"output":106,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36132,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776387759429,"responseId":"resp_06c3af14b50a39800169e186b06840819bb137c5d1b7ee8848"}}
