{"type":"message","id":"ada74f64","parentId":"5d09ea4a","timestamp":"2026-04-17T02:46:59.872Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Understanding the pipeline**\n\nThis configuration shows that the system is using `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.csv` as the primary source. The note says \"fallback = web/manual source when ledger IDs empty.\" This suggests that when web source is not available, it falls back to manual source.\n\nThe problem is that `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is stale (from April 14). The user might want to:\n1. Refresh this file using their THS Level2 interface\n2. Or change the pipeline to always use THS Level2 interface directly instead of relying on a cached file\n\nLet me check if there's a script that generates `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json`. Look for scripts that might sync holdings."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_P98RRSN1uWZkszQGEhzhfx4j","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system -name \"*.py\" -exec grep -l \"ths_web_selected_holdings\\|sync.*holdings\" {} \\; 2>/dev/null | head -n 50","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":170,"output":312,"cacheRead":81600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82082,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776394008413,"responseId":"3b451496-0e28-44ac-902e-2a57d9dad513"}}
