{"type":"message","id":"4995dddf","parentId":"98dd5854","timestamp":"2026-04-17T03:02:56.227Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see there are web-based holdings files from March 8, 2026. These are much older than the local app data. It seems the web-based holdings pipeline might not be running regularly.\n\nNow, let me think about what the user actually wants. They said \"把 web source fusion 的源改成 Level2 接口\" (Change the web source fusion's source to Level2 interface).\n\nThere are two interpretations:\n1. **Use THS Level2 for real-time data in the fusion report** - The fusion report might use real-time quotes from Level2 for current prices\n2. **Use THS Level2 as the source for holdings data** - This doesn't make sense because Level2 doesn't provide holdings data\n\nGiven the context, I think the user might want the fusion report to use real-time Level2 data for current prices, not change the holdings source. But they specifically said \"web source fusion\", which uses `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` as input.\n\nLet me check what the web source fusion actually does. Let me search for the web source fusion script."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fvArueJKye2NaecqLJSqViqb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system -name \"*.py\" -exec grep -l \"web_source_fusion\" {} \\; 2>/dev/null","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":628,"output":362,"cacheRead":79232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776394960517,"responseId":"985dc6cc-9343-48e5-a9ed-037ab12029ae"}}
